snippet.textDisplay: I think the reason why season 2 and Joe's relationship with Love hit the same notes is because it's meant to represent something. I mean, the girl isn't called Love just cos it was a nice name. It's because this entire thing is meant to represent Joe's relationship with love as a concept. He finds a girl, he worms his way into their life by any means necessary, and then something awful happens at the end. He's done this with Candace and Beck already - met them, loved them, killed them. However (spoiler alert), in season 2, Love turns out to be as much of a killer as he is. Love is just as scary as Joe's obsession with it, and his entire relationship with her represents how Joe is stuck in a loop with an idea that is lethal.

snippet.textDisplay: The point of the fake out was to show us how Will sees himself because he is so oblivious to the fact his behavior is horrendously unhealthy. He can live 75% of his life as a normal person without even acknowledging the atrocities he's committed because he is a sociopath. He lacks any and all guilt and only thinks about it when it is necessary. It is like when we remember we have bills to pay. His version is "I have self preservation to attend to" like getting rid of the people he's killed. I thought it was an impressive way to portray his mental illness. I wish tv shows would do a better job of showing what it is like to have mental illnesses and not just showing people with them. They gave a whole hell of a lot of empathy to a murderer but meh they're tryin. Love your vids. I've watched every one
